To make mushroom and cheese sauce, you'll need the following ingredients:

* 1 lb. cremini mushrooms, sliced
* 1/2 lb. butter
* 1/2 cup heavy cream
* 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese
* Salt and pepper to taste
* 1 tbsp. dried thyme
* Fresh parsley for garnish

In a large skillet over medium heat, melt the butter. Add the sliced mushrooms and sauté until they release their juices and start to brown, about 5-7 minutes. Stir in the heavy cream, Parmesan cheese, salt, and pepper. Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook until the sauce has thickened, about 5-7 minutes more. Stir in the dried thyme and fresh parsley. Serve hot over pasta or with meat.
